The market is showing strong signs of bullish sentiment, coupled with the falling US interest rate.

If you're looking for promising narratives to follow before the surge begins, here are some good options:

1️⃣ #Meme 

The Meme narrative has been a winner in both bullish and bearish market durations of the cycle.

Tokens to watch: $Pepe, $Dog, $Cat, $Neiro.

2️⃣ #AI 

The intersection of AI and crypto has been gaining significant attention. 
Following the surge of AI in Tradefi, AI in crypto is poised for a significant impact.

Tokens to watch: $RNDR, $TAO, $ASI, $IO, $ATH.

3️⃣ #DeFi Blue Chips 

The DeFi narrative is expected to make a comeback, particularly the OG Defi protocols that are mature and play an important role in the Blockchain space.

Tokens to watch: $AAVE, $UNI, $COMP, $LDO, $CRV.

4️⃣ #Layer1 

As a foundational layer of blockchain, Layer 1s always attract users due to their innovation, speed, security, and cost-effectiveness.
Tokens to watch: $SUI, $SEI, $SOL, $APT, $KAS

5️⃣ #RWA 

Real World Asset (RWA) is estimated to reach $16 trillion by 2030, making it a strong catalyst for crypto adoption.

Tokens to watch: $ONDO, $RIO, $MPL, $CPOOL.

6️⃣ #Telegram Mini-app 

The Telegram Mini app narrative has gained significant strength, with millions of new users joining the Web3 space. 
Binance has demonstrated strong support for TG MiniApp’s token listing.

Tokens to watch: $TON, $NOT, $DOGS, $HMSTR, $CATI.

If you’re already spending time in #DeFi, it’s worth watching what @TheoriqAI is doing with @TheoRooAI.

They’ve created an #AI-native strategist persona, an onchain kangaroo with alpha in his pouch and coordination in his code. He’s here to swarm.

Theo Roo acts as an interface layer between users and a swarm of autonomous agents doing real #onchain work.

It starts with agents that are already watching #Uniswap data, analyzing volatility, drafting LP strategies, and executing swaps completely autonomously.

But instead of just dropping docs and diagrams, #Theoriq built a character that explains it all in meme-speak, strategy lingo, and real-time updates.

That’s the interesting part to me. Most mascots just sit on top of the brand. Theo Roo is the brand and the strategy layer. He talks to you like a founder would in DMs, but with data pipelines and LP logic behind it.

And if you’re wondering what he’s working on next?

Well, he’s already coordinating with forecasting models, tapping into @graphprotocol data, listening to vibes from @cookiedotfun, and figuring out how LPs can finally rest while agents rebalance the bag.

In a narrative where protocols need faces, agents need voice, and strategy needs story, Theo Roo is what happens when you combine all three.
Truly pushing boundaries instead of just riding trends.
